#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn10.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga "
msgstr "1. With Indaka "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn10.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Sūcilomasutta "
msgstr "3. With Spiky "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.207, sc1
msgctxt "sn10.3:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā gayāyaṃ viharati ṭaṅkitamañce sūcilomassa yakkhassa bhavane. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Gayā on the cut-stone ledge in the haunt of Spiky the native spirit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.3:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena kharo ca yakkho sūcilomo ca yakkho bhagavato avidūre atikkamanti. "
msgstr "Now at that time the native spirits Shaggy and Spiky were passing by not far from the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.3:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho kharo yakkho sūcilomaṃ yakkhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "So Shaggy said to Spiky, "

msgctxt "sn10.3:1.4"
msgid "“eso samaṇo”ti. "
msgstr "“That’s an ascetic.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.3:1.5"
msgid "“Neso samaṇo, samaṇako eso. "
msgstr "“That’s no ascetic, he’s a faker! "

msgctxt "sn10.3:1.6"
msgid "Yāva jānāmi yadi vā so samaṇo yadi vā pana so samaṇako”ti. "
msgstr "I’ll soon find out whether he’s an ascetic or a faker.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.446, sc2
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho sūcilomo yakkho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato kāyaṃ upanāmesi. "
msgstr "Then Spiky went up to the Buddha and leaned up against his body, "

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā kāyaṃ apanāmesi. "
msgstr "but the Buddha pulled away. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho sūcilomo yakkho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Spiky said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.4"
msgid "“bhāyasi maṃ, samaṇā”ti? "
msgstr "“Are you afraid, ascetic?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.5"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ taṃ, āvuso, bhāyāmi; "
msgstr "“No, sir, I’m not afraid. "

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.6"
msgid "api ca te samphasso pāpako”ti. "
msgstr "But your touch is nasty.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.7"
msgid "“Pañhaṃ taṃ, samaṇa, pucchissāmi. "
msgstr "“I will ask you a question, ascetic. "

# NOTE: Considering the Ganges is 100km away, this is even more impressive!
#. VAR: pāragaṅgāya → pāraṃ gaṅgāya (mr)
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.8"
msgid "Sace me na byākarissasi, cittaṃ vā te khipissāmi, hadayaṃ vā te phālessāmi, pādesu vā gahetvā pāragaṅgāya khipissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "If you don’t answer me, I’ll drive you insane, or explode your heart, or grab you by the feet and throw you to the far shore of the Ganges!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.9"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ taṃ, āvuso, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya, yo me cittaṃ vā khipeyya hadayaṃ vā phāleyya pādesu vā gahetvā pāragaṅgāya khipeyya; "
msgstr "“I don’t see anyone in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans who could do that to me. "

#. VAR: () → (atha kho sūcilomo yakkho bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi.) (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.10"
msgid "api ca tvaṃ, āvuso, puccha yadā kaṅkhasī”ti. () "
msgstr "But anyway, ask what you wish.” "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3, verse-num-sc808
msgctxt "sn10.3:3.1"
msgid "“Rāgo ca doso ca kutonidānā, "
msgstr "“Where do greed and hate come from? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:3.2"
msgid "Aratī ratī lomahaṃso kutojā; "
msgstr "From where do discontent, desire, and terror spring? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:3.3"
msgid "Kuto samuṭṭhāya manovitakkā, "
msgstr "Where do the mind’s thoughts originate, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:3.4"
msgid "Kumārakā dhaṅkamivossajantī”ti. "
msgstr "like a crow let loose by boys.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, verse-num-sc809
msgctxt "sn10.3:4.1"
msgid "“Rāgo ca doso ca itonidānā, "
msgstr "“Greed and hate come from here; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:4.2"
msgid "Aratī ratī lomahaṃso itojā; "
msgstr "from here spring discontent, desire, and terror; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:4.3"
msgid "Ito samuṭṭhāya manovitakkā, "
msgstr "here’s where the mind’s thoughts originate, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:4.4"
msgid "Kumārakā dhaṅkamivossajanti. "
msgstr "like a crow let loose by boys. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.447, sc5, verse-num-sc810
msgctxt "sn10.3:5.1"
msgid "Snehajā attasambhūtā, "
msgstr "Born of affection, originating in oneself, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:5.2"
msgid "nigrodhasseva khandhajā; "
msgstr "like the shoots from a banyan’s trunk; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:5.3"
msgid "Puthū visattā kāmesu, "
msgstr "the many kinds of attachment to sensual pleasures "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: vitatā → vitthatā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn10.3:5.4"
msgid "māluvāva vitatā vane. "
msgstr "are like camel’s foot creeper strung through the woods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.208, sc6, verse-num-sc811
msgctxt "sn10.3:6.1"
msgid "Ye naṃ pajānanti yatonidānaṃ, "
msgstr "Those who understand where they come from "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:6.2"
msgid "Te naṃ vinodenti suṇohi yakkha; "
msgstr "get rid of them—listen up, spirit! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:6.3"
msgid "Te duttaraṃ oghamimaṃ taranti, "
msgstr "They cross this flood so hard to cross, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:6.4"
msgid "Atiṇṇapubbaṃ apunabbhavāyā”ti. "
msgstr "not crossed before, so as to not be reborn.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
